@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
The ultimate in weird utilities.  A cli based program to search for web pages
containing keywords.  Currently, it only talks to altavista and only does a
simple query.

Program was written so I could do searches for web pages without firing up
a browser on the amiga.  Not useful at all for most people, but then, I didn't
write it for anyone else but myself.

If you happen to be one of the people that finds this program strangely useful
, or want a specially tweaked version, then please email me and tell me so.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"

USAGE

websearch count word1 word2 word3 ... word8

    - 'count' is in the range 1 to 50 and is the number of matches output
        (multiples of 10 matches are received but you may not want all 10 output)
        (I can't see anyone using this wanting to match more than 50. If you
        desperately *do* want to match more than this either write me some nice
        email or just use a web browser)

    - If you leave out 'count', websearch defaults to count=10

    - 'word?' are the words to match in the search.

    - Only matches 8 words currently, but this is easily expandable.  I don't know
        if it's worth making the number of words matched higher. (Email me
        if you desperatly want it)

    - For every extra lot of 10 matches it has to make, websearch has to
        hit the altavista page again, thus slowing it down.

    - See @{"appendix" link "Appendix"} for a bit on the altavista search engine and how to get
        better matches.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

REQUIREMENTS
    - a net connection. (I'm using it on amitcp4.0.  If it works on mlink or
        anything else let me know)
    - ixemul43+ and ixnet1+ libraries
    - don't know about a stack usage. If it freaks out, then try a larger stack
        (has successfuly been run on 4096 stack.)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Problems" "Problems"

PROBLEMS
    - bugger all errorchecking.  If it can't connect to altavista it'll still
        pretend that everything's ok.
    - if you have problems with websearch, check the requirements (set stack to
        50000 (This is just so you can eliminate stacksize as one of your
        problems) and check the versions of your libraries).
    - E-mail me and tell me the symptoms and your setup if you get weird probs
        (cpu/fpu/machine/stack/type of net connection etc)
    - uses a really dodgy method to extract URLs from altavista output. This
        will certainly break if/when altavista change their output. Inform me
        if they do.
    - sometimes prints out weird cgi-bin links from altavista.  This is due
        again to the dodgy way I extract URLs.

@ENDNODE

