@NODE "Appendix" "Appendix"

alta vista search tips (all shamelessly stolen from the altavista site)

    - quotation marks will force altavista to look for a matching phrase
           eg "fluid dynamics" will look for that phrase, not the separate
           occurence of those words within a document.

    - match words which are required are prefixed by '+'

    - match words which are prohibited are prefixed by '-'
        eg websearch 10 +film -noir
                will find matches for 'film' that do not contain 'noir'

    - the wildcard * may be used, but i'm not sure in all contexts.
        eg websearch 10 draw*
                will match draws, drawing, drawn etc
        *NOT WORKING CORRECTLY IN WEBSEARCH*
        Only seems to want to work if you don't have a trailing *
        ie   This works:   websearch 10 sandman* junk
             This doesn't: websearch 10 junk sandman*

    - if you have a search word in mixed case, or in a different case from
        the other search words, altavista will implement a case-sensitive
        search


websearch oddity:  Searching for a required phrase.
    If you search for a phrase which is required in a match with AltaVista
    you use
                +"get a dog"

    But due to the dodgy way I got around handling " characters, the
    format for the equivalent search in websearch would be
            websearch 10 "+get a dog"

@ENDNODE
